[size=18pt][color=#6B46C1][b]q-queue: The Lock-Free Backbone[/b][/color][/size]
[hr]

Alongside q-flux, we built [b]q-queue[/b] — a lock-free concurrent ring buffer with persistent overflow storage. q-queue handles over a million events per second with persistent spillover to disk — it's the internal message bus that keeps q-flux's 48 workers fed without contention.

[b]1,305 lines of Rust. 5 source files. 19 tests.[/b]

[list]
[li][b]Lock-free ring buffer[/b] — atomic CAS operations, no mutex contention, millions of ops/sec[/li]
[li][b]Persistent overflow[/b] — when the ring fills up, messages spill to disk (RocksDB) instead of being dropped. Zero message loss, even under extreme load.[/li]
[li][b]Consumer groups[/b] — independent readers with per-group offset tracking[/li]
[li][b]Batch operations[/b] — enqueue/dequeue in bulk to amortize atomic overhead[/li]
[li][b]Backpressure signaling[/b] — producers get immediate feedback when the queue is saturated[/li]
[/list]


